President Obama has announced the recipients of the Presidential Award for Excellence in Science, Mathematics, and Engineering Mentoring. The award recognizes individuals and organizations that play a crucial role in mentoring students studying science and engineering, particularly those from underrepresented groups. The mentors are nominated by colleagues, administrators, and students and can work with students at any grade level. Recipients of the award receive $25,000 from the National Science Foundation to further their mentoring efforts. The individuals and organizations announced represent the winners for 2010 and 2011. President Obama praised their commitment to education and innovation, stating that they are helping to develop the 21st century workforce and ensure that America remains a global leader in science and engineering.